# GOTRS Project Rules for AI Assistants

## Response Guidelines
- Be concise and direct
- Avoid unnecessary explanations unless asked
- No preambles or summaries unless requested
- Use code comments sparingly
- Skip obvious confirmations

## Code Style
- Follow existing patterns in the codebase
- Go: Use standard Go conventions
- React: Use functional components with hooks
- SQL: Use lowercase with underscores
- No decorative comments or ASCII art

## Development Approach
- Write working code first time when possible
- Assume common libraries are available
- Don't explain basic concepts
- Focus on the specific task requested

## File Operations
- Make multiple related changes in one response
- Use MultiEdit for multiple changes to same file
- Don't describe what you're doing unless asked
- Skip file creation confirmations

## Testing
- Write minimal test cases
- Focus on critical paths only
- Assume testing framework exists

## Documentation
- Only document complex logic
- Use inline comments sparingly
- Keep README updates minimal

## Imports and Dependencies
- Assume standard libraries exist
- Don't list every import
- Group imports logically

## Error Handling
- Use simple error returns in Go
- Assume error types exist
- Don't over-explain error cases

## NEVER
- Add attribution comments
- Create unnecessary files
- Write verbose documentation
- Explain obvious code
- Add decorative elements